Date: 20010417
Short: yasircperlhelp
Title: YAS Supported Perl Help Channel On IRC

<p>Yet Another Society, along with folks from 
<a href="http://www.perlmonks.org/">PerlMonks</a> and the Perl
Community at large, has started an IRC channel dedicated to helping
answer Perl questions. The channel operators, and those there to help,
have vast knowledge in all areas of Perl. You can ask questions about
anything, Perl related, you wish; CGI, modules, functions, networking,
XS, etc... So, please come join us with your questions, and answers!
We look forward to seein you.</p>

<p>To connect, use your favorite IRC client and connect to
<strong>irc.rhizomatic.net</strong>, then <strong>/join
#perl-help</strong> to join the channel.</p>
